'''Climax Uranium Mill''' is a decommissioned [[uranium]] mill near [[Grand Junction, CO]].

The mill, that processed vanadium as well as uranium, was incorporated May 11, 1950. It was constructed on city-owned property next to the Colorado River which was once the Grand Junction sugar beet mill. Climax Uranium Company gutted the former sugar beet mill, removing any remaining equipment and stabilizing weak walls, and began uranium and [[vanadium]] milling operations. The mill soon grew to be 12 buildings large and processed 2 million tons of ore, mostly for the [[United States Atomic Energy Commission]].<ref name="rmoa">{{cite web| url = http://ahc.uwyo.edu/usearchives/inventories/html/wyu-ah09832.html#d0e73| title = Inventory of the Climax Uranium Mill records, 1942-1976| accessdate = 2011-01-26| year = 2006| work = Rocky Mountain Online Archive}}</ref>

==Decommissioning==
From the early 1950s to 1966, Climax donated approximately 300,000 tons of radioactive [[uranium tailings]] to the city of Grand Junction for use as a construction material.<ref name=Grammer>{{Citation|last1 =Grammer|first1=Elisa J.|title = The Uranium Mill Tailings Radiation Control Act of 1978 and NRC's Agreement State Program|journal = ''Natural Resources Lawyer''|volume = 13|issue = 3|pages = 469–522 [481]|year = 1981|jstor =40922651|ref=Grammer}}</ref> The tailings were used in sewer and road construction. In 1972, Congress gave the Atomic Energy Commission authority to cooperate with Grand Junction in a cleanup operation, with the federal government covering 75% of the project's cost.{{sfn|Grammer|1981|479}}

The mill was decommissioned in 1970 under the [[US Department of Energy|US Department of Energy's]] [[Uranium Mill Tailings Remedial Action]] project.<ref name="doe">{{cite web| url = http://www.em.doe.gov/bemr/BEMRSites/gjus.aspx|title= Grand Junction, Colorado (Umtra Site)| accessdate = 2012-12-17|publisher=Department of Energy}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://clui.org/ludb/site/grand-junction-climax-uranium-mill-site|accessdate=December 17, 2012|publisher=The Center for Land Use Interpretation|title=GRAND JUNCTION CLIMAX URANIUM MILL SITE}}</ref> The mill site was designated for [[environmental remediation]] by the [[Uranium Mill Tailings Radiation Control Act]] in 1978.{{sfn|Grammer|1981|479}}

==Restoration==
The [[Nuclear Regulatory Commission]] published a Remedial Action Plan for the site in 1994, and the removal of 4.5 million cubic yards of contaminated materials from the site to a disposal cell was completed that spring.<ref name=doe/> Reseeding and wetlands establishment was completed in August 1994.

