'''Cobblestone Street''', also known as '''Fifth Street''' and '''Main Street''', is a historic [[cobblestone]] [[street]] located at [[Boonville, Missouri|Boonville]], [[Cooper County, Missouri]]. It was built about 1832, and was part of the original Fifth or Main Street.  It is located beneath the Boonville Road Bridge and is constructed of cobblestones of varying sizes.  The street remnant is approximately 20 feet wide and approximately 200 feet long.  The street connected the main commercial district of Boonville with the wharves along the [[Missouri River]].<ref name="DNR">{{cite web| url =http://www.dnr.mo.gov/shpo/nps-nr/82005293.pdf| title = National Register of Historic Places Inventory Nomination Form: Cobblestone Street| accessdate = 2016-11-01| author=Preservation Planning Section|format = PDF| date=May 1989|publisher=Missouri Department of Natural Resources}}] (includes 3 photos from 1988)</ref>{{rp|2-3}}

It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 1990.<ref name=nris/>

